That was only a formatting change. Let me evaluate more carefully whether combining the two passes would actually improve clarity. A combined reduce would look like:

```typescript
const { totalDamage, hasDragonDamage } = incident.damages.reduce(
  (acc, d) => ({ totalDamage: acc.totalDamage + d.amount, hasDragonDamage: acc.hasDragonDamage || d.material === "dragon" }),
  { totalDamage: 0, hasDragonDamage: false }
);
```

This is harder to read and more mass overall (object accumulator). Rule 2 trumps APP — keep separate passes for clarity.

The formatting refactoring (multiline ternary) is the only improvement that helps without hurting clarity. Let me verify it still passes:

